<TITLE> 'Outstanding talent' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)Dr M A Wazed Miah was a natural talent, his university teacher Dr Ajoy Roy said. While reminiscing about the past with bdnews24.com, Dr. Roy regarded Miah as a person endowed with outstanding talent. Dr Miah died on Saturday afternoon after long fighting for life at Square Hospital. "Wazed was a very brilliant student of physics department in earlier career." A theoretical physicist, Dr Miah obtained Ph. D degree from Imperial College London. "He joined (Bangladesh) Atomic Energy Commission as a junior scientist on completion of education with academic excellence, first class both in honours and master's examinations" "Then he flew to London for doing Ph. D with scholarship. Afterwards, he came back home and joined the then mass movement (against Pakistani rulers) on return from abroad." Dr. Roy added. bd
